<p>Studying algorithms and data structures by Miller and Ranum (2011) I came across binary tree abstract data type (ADT). It is an ingenious device, where its Yes/No or 0/1 choice paths lead to many useful implementations. As I drew a binary tree for an assignment, I thought, why not try to implement a ternary tree ADT, with three choice paths instead of two. It would be such a novel idea, wouldn’t it?</p>

